**Bug Pattern: State Object Replacement Race Condition**

When a state object has multiple properties managed by different methods, replacing the entire object can cause race conditions where one update overwrites another.

**Problem:**
```javascript
// BAD - Creates new object, can overwrite isOpen set by another method
this.panelState = {
  left: Math.round(rect.left),
  isOpen: this.panelState.isOpen  // ‚Üê Can be stale
};
```

**Solution:**
```javascript
// GOOD - Update properties directly, preserves other properties
this.panelState.left = Math.round(rect.left);
// Note: isOpen NOT touched - only setIsOpen() should modify it
```

**Key Principle:** Separation of concerns - different aspects of state (position/size vs visibility) should be updated independently.
